HIS past with young women may be fishy.&nbsp;But like the catch of the day . . .THE KING OF SUSHI HAS BEEN HOOKED!In a riveting saga littered with some of Mzansi&rsquo;s most intriguing tales of sex, champagne and house music, Nonkululeko Whitney Mhlanga (22) has pulled off what many would have considered impossible.That&rsquo;s because this stunning makoti-to-be is getting married to one of Mzansi&rsquo;s most high-profile playboys, Kenny Kunene.And this after the 46-year-old allegedly vowed never to set foot down the aisle following a &ldquo;nasty divorce&rdquo; from his childhood sweetheart.And it gets better! This happily-ever-after fairytale of beauty and the beast includes Baby Sushi, a bouncing bundle of joy in the making.When contacted for comment, an eager Kenny could not contain his excitement.&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve changed my philandering ways of using women for sex, and can&rsquo;t wait to live the rest of my life with my darling,&rdquo; Kenny said.&ldquo;When I met Nonkululeko, I thought she would also be one of my victims, but her beautiful soul and heart really changed my heart. I truly fell head over heels in love with her!&rdquo;Singing nothing but praises for his squeeze, Kenny said a day without Nonkululeko felt like a lifetime.Said a proud Kenny: &ldquo;She&rsquo;s held my hand and showed me the way without being bossy and arrogant. I love her more for that.&ldquo;I wanted to marry her two years ago, but she asked that she complete her studies first, so I honoured her wish. Now we&rsquo;re here.&rdquo;Citing how inseparable the couple was, the King of Sushi said age was just a number.&ldquo;Our forefathers used to marry women 20 or 30 years younger than them, that&rsquo;s why those marriages lasted. I&rsquo;m really happy and in a good space, that&rsquo;s all that matters. Forget the age,&rdquo; he said.According to sources close to the couple, the alleged 11 March wedding would be a traditional ceremony.&ldquo;They&rsquo;ll take care of umembeso first,&rdquo; the first source said.Said the second source: &ldquo;Kenny&rsquo;s family will bring gifts to their new bride&rsquo;s family, and in the afternoon, Kenny will get introduced to his in-laws traditionally.&rdquo;Asked for comment, a mellow Nonkululeko kept her statement brief: &ldquo;It&rsquo;s a personal matter for me, and I prefer to keep it that way.&rdquo;Kenny&rsquo;s controversies include publicly declaring his support for Oscar Pistorius and recently launching Weekly Xpos&eacute;, an online news platform.